The paper deals with dynamic gesture recognition, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The proposed technique involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also mentions the use of soft-attention, which is a technique commonly used in natural language processing (cs.IR) but has also been applied in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CV and cs.HC, followed by cs.MM, cs.LG, and cs.IR.
